'''Alaikai Trotter''' was a [[Historian/Legends|historian]] who resided on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Trotter had an intimate familiarity with the planet's history and that of its inhabitants. One of Trotter's most notable works was the study of the life and legacy of the famed Tatooinian [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Sidrona Diath]].<ref name="SWG:DS">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=terminal||Diath's Shadow}} on Tatooine</ref> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> Alaikai Trotter recruited a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] to fight dangerous creatures that infested the desert of Tatooine and protect the inhabitants of the planet like Sidrona Diath did thousand years before.<ref name="SWG:DS" />

==Behind the scenes==
Alaikai Trotter was first mentioned in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:DS" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> Alaikai Trotter was mentioned in the mission "Diath's Shadow" that is available to players at mission terminals on Tatooine. Trotter hired the player to follow Diath's example and "free Tatooine from the monsters that infest the desert". The player had to destroy a random creature lair and several creatures to accomplish the mission.<ref name="SWG:DS" />

